strings: A well-known monster commonly encountered throughout the world. Quite intelligent. Some have even managed to learn the human tongue.
A happy-go-lucky, good-natured monster. Born with only one stripe, it grows another with each passing year.
A slug-like creature with distinctively large lips. They seem to greet one another with big, sloppy kisses!
A bat-like monster that flies freely through the night sky. According to one account, they're born in a world without light.
The large horns above each ear fall off and grow back every year. The hornpipes they carry are carved from their old horns.
A distinctive monster shaped like a pepper. In their culture, two is always better than one, so they stick together with the help of a large skewer!
A rabbit-like monster with a distinctive single horn growing from the middle of its forehead. Unlike normal rabbits, they are determinedly carnivorous, using their sharp horns to spear prey.
Slimes of a different colour, apparently due to a sudden mutation. Although commonly referred to as ‘she-slimes’, their true gender remains unknown.
Small but seriously strong. Once they psyche themselves up, these pint-sized pests can inflict some disproportionately drastic damage.
The mechanical bodies of these birds weigh more than Yangus after a big dinner! They have a tendency to snap the tree branches where they roost and fall to earth with a metallic clunk.
These sticky masses of muck are poisonous to the touch. Once a traveller comes into contact with a bubble slime's body in battle, the effects of the poison will persist until the individual is cured.
A race of demons wearing what appear to be bright blue kecks. They are rumoured to drop them when defeated!
Diminutive but resourceful monsters. Upon encountering an enemy, they keep their distance and let fly with long-range bow and arrow attacks.
A hairy fur ball of a monster whose love for unwanted old boots manifests itself in much the same way as a hermit crab's love for discarded shells.

Related to the dracky, these monsters have evolved a green colouration to match their woodland habitat. They remain constantly airborne, smoothly dodging attacks whilst casting spells on their opponents.
Despite their weighty appearance, these insectoid monsters are quite swift. They like to tackle their opponents head-on with the help of their huge horns.
Juvenile forms of elite magical monsters. Imps try to cast spells which are far too powerful for them and fail every time.
Mushroom-shaped monsters with a sweet breath that puts enemies to sleep. They grow in humid areas like grasslands and deep forests.
These foppish fiends leave foes floundering with their flamboyant foil-work. When not showing off their skill with a sword, they like to demonstrate their dazzling dancing.
A kindly slime that never hesitates to help comrades by casting healing spells, even when in danger itself. All in all, a supportive little monster.

Not the largest monster in the world, but amongst the strongest. Their bodies seem even smaller next to the massive wooden mallets they carry. The unwieldiness of these weapons means they frequently miss.
A feline monster with stripes reminiscent of a jailhouse convict. Strangely popular among cat lovers. Usually quite playful, but capable of casting spells when provoked.
Though quite weak in frog form, their attacks become far more dangerous when they reveal the human faces on their backs.
Physically quite weak, but capable of wearing enemies down by repeatedly casting unpleasant spells. Occasionally splits into two when losing a battle.
An odd monster in the form of an eyeball with arms and legs. Said to turn red and become very strong when angered.
Ignore their cuddly appearance. These monsters are actually ruthless adversaries, capable of decreasing an enemy's tension whilst raising their own.
Bulldog-like monsters that throw their spiked collars to ensnare enemies and make them easier to hit.
A large moth-like monster that flies freely through the air on giant wings. Capable of casting air-based spells on groups of enemies simultaneously.
A monster shaped like a large bell. Usually does nothing more than watch and laugh, but occasionally calls jargons for help.
Physically quite imposing, these monsters are also capable of breathing fire and throwing magical sand from their jars. They appear to enjoy a symbiotic relationship with dingalings.
Drackymas are the mothers of drackies. The lullabies they use to put their babies to sleep work just as well against their foes in battle.
Powerful bird-like monsters that resemble two-legged bulls. Sleepy and lethargic, they are foul-tempered when suddenly awakened.
Despite their silly appearance, these monsters are crafty opponents capable of preventing enemies from casting spells.
Human knights that met a foul and painful end. Frustration and sadness at their pitiful fate keeps them in this world as undead monsters.

Popular among adventurers for the inordinately large number of experience points they bestow. Although not particularly dangerous, their tendency to flee at the first sign of trouble makes them difficult to defeat.
Enormous scorpions with impenetrable carapaces. Their defences protect them against all but the most determined physical attacks. Use magic to defeat them.
Mushroom-shaped monsters with a sweet breath that puts enemies to sleep. Commonly encountered in humid areas such as deep forests and grasslands.
Usually calm and timid, these monsters psyche themselves up to become vicious foes when provoked. Their tiny bodies conceal incredible power.
A mutant fly grown to human size. Known to carry rare treasures.
A unique monster that delights in telling its opponents stories using hand-puppets.
Great archers in spite of their size. Capable of surrounding opponents and unleashing a fusillade of arrows upon them. When trouble beckons, they swiftly call for reinforcements.
Monsters that skulk around in the dead of night. They are masters of defensive magic and can deflect enemy spells.
A monster wrapped from head to toe in filthy old bandages. Capable of spitting curses that envelop and immobilise enemies.
A monster hornet with a paralysing sting. Be sure to carry moonwort bulbs with you if you think you will encounter these vicious monsters.
Half man, half goat, and the worst of both. Usually timid, they turn red if provoked and call for fellow pan pipers to join the fray.
Angry at seeing their slime<->friends bullied by swaggering adventurers, these courageous little monsters swore an oath to defend them. Now they roam the land as knights on slime steeds!
These mechanical birds are the result of a mad scientist's twisted experiment. When they detect a target, they become a deadly whirlwind of razor-sharp blades.
Rightly feared for their habit of hiding in forests and ambushing travellers. When hurt, they pluck leaves from their own branches to use as healing herbs.
Wet and glistening monsters said to carry various moulds that can be used to make special cheeses.
Mysterious monsters known for wearing eerie masks. Their real faces are said to be even scarier.
As the name implies, a monstrous rotten corpse. Their foul appearance can cause your tension to decrease suddenly.
Heavyweight monsters that dive-bomb opponents, body<->slamming them to the ground.
Extremely agile, these monsters are feared for their skilful rapier-work and Mercurial Thrusts.
A pair of psychotic peppers. Their crazed grins belie their wiliness in battle. They can prevent enemies from using spells, and like to pummel their adversaries with body-slams.
The wings of these monsters are useful items that allow travellers to teleport to previously visited locations instantly.
Mysterious masked monsters with a nasty habit of hacking down unwary travellers. These vain creatures love to flex their muscles and psyche up in front of their enemies.
Known for their jumping ability, these monsters wait for the best opportunity to attack their enemies. Watch out for their vicious slashes and formidable defensive abilities.
A surprisingly powerful monster. Its cute looks betray no hint that it is skilled at both fire and ice magic.
A brute of a monster that wields a club to bash enemies. Even a single blow can inflict tremendous damage.
A crude figure fashioned out of mud and animated with a magical spell. Dances a strange dance that lowers the MP of opponents.

A skilful mimic that disguises itself as a treasure chest. It waits quietly to be discovered, then chomps on unwary travellers with its sharp fangs. Occasionally capable of landing devastating attacks.

An enchanted bag of treasure<->turned<->monster.
Highly resistant to almost every spell, except those that drain its magic.
A sexy she-monster that seduces enemies with her Puff-Puff ability before unleashing a barrage of spells on her hapless foes.
A cursed monster that continues to suffer even in death. As an undead creature, it hates the living and attacks travellers on sight.
As the name implies, this is a slime capable of casting powerful curative magic. Defeat it quickly or it will heal its weaker comrades during battle.
The angry soul of a dead swordsman inhabiting an empty suit of armour. Occasionally summons healslimes to assist it in battle.
A ragged cape enchanted by powerful magic. Invulnerable to air-based spells.
A gorgeous hunk of a demon that spins and uses its thorny tail as a whip.
A strange creature with an eerie laugh. When you hear it, you know it's about to self-destruct.
A monster with a gleaming golden coat. Seems obsessed with collecting shiny objects.
A horrifying mud-monster that lives in the depths of the earth. Extends a hand above ground to pull travellers to their doom.
A feline monster that spends its days lazing about. In battle, its sleepiness can be contagious.
A foul insect-monster from the underworld. Spits and sprays poison at its enemies.
A short-tempered and aggressive monster. Psyches up and launches powerful body-slam attacks.
The combined form of mum, boh, jum, and boe. Rattles opponents by casting Boom and using earth-shaking physical attacks.
Deadly machines designed to hunt down and exterminate monsters of the metal family. If you encounter one, chances are a certain highly desirable metal monster may be in the area...
Far more agile than they appear, these monsters are harder to hit than you might think. Their clubs pack a powerful punch.
Hunted by adventurers all over the world. Their bodies consist of a mysterious gel-like metal.
Capable of extremely powerful attacks when psyched up. Beware of mad moles who are in a state of high tension!
Flower-monsters nourished by the anguish of those unfortunate enough to be turned into thorny vines, such as the residents of Trodain Castle.
Monsters that attack their enemies from the sky. Rumour has it that they can cast spells capable of wiping out entire parties, but the truth remains unknown.
Ambulatory suits of cursed armour. Beware their swords. When driven into the ground, they can stun a group of adversaries with powerful lightning bolts.
Thorny rose bushes turned into monsters by Dhoulmagus. Whenever one is killed, another is born to take its place.
Quick-witted dog monsters. Their loud barks serve to intimidate the enemy and summon allies.
Mysterious and unpredictable monsters. Don't let their small size fool you. They are more powerful than they appear.
A race of swordsmen...or should that be ‘swordschickens’? They boast powerful sword skills and mastery of the Wind Sickles attack.
Fearless, highly agile predators with sharp fangs. Rumour has it that they can be tamed, but the truth remains unknown.
Brave slime-knights who live for a fight. Although resistant to attack spells, they are susceptible to support spells.
A strangely theatrical monster. Performs a carefully prepared puppet show, entitled ‘Love Story’, that stirs up the enemy in all sorts of ways.
The dazzling bodies of these monsters burn as fiercely as the surface of the sun. They spew fire at their enemies.
Capable of firing huge volleys of poisoned arrows simultaneously, these monsters also carry antidotal herbs in case they accidentally stick themselves.
Damages foes with poison needles while adroitly dodging incoming attacks. Rumour has it that a sting from this monster can cause paralysis.
Boar-like monsters with masterful spear technique. Their Achilles heel is their low agility.
A nocturnal monster that occasionally appears alongside goodybags in forested areas.
Said to carry Yggdrasil leaves in their treetops, these monsters have the ability to resurrect fallen comrades.
The armoured pink carapaces of these insect monsters are highly resistant to physical attacks and spells. Try using magic to lower their defence before attacking.
Obnoxious magicians with a penchant for casting spells to confuse their opponents. For an easier battle, stop their magic with a well-placed spell of your own.
Former knights enslaved by the power of the Lord of Darkness. Loyal to the core, they continue to fight even in death.
Nocturnal monsters that can freely fly through the air. Their preferred style of attack is to dive-bomb enemies from high altitude.
Famed for their fancy footwork, these monsters use a variety of dance attacks during battle. See if you can spot them all!
Man-eating mushroom monsters that live in shady forests. They cast ice magic to freeze unwary travellers and then use them as fertiliser.
A cruel race of demons that cast instant-death spells in an attempt to consign their foes to an early grave.
Vicious beasts whose obsession with bodybuilding has turned them into even more formidable foes. Use spells to level the playing field.
Golden creatures that have taken it upon themselves to protect the Holy Isle of Neos and the Goddess statue erected there.
The result of many small slimes fusing together and bestowing themselves with a crown. A slime with royal aspirations!
The iron carapaces of these fearsome creatures are virtually impervious to sword attacks, but they are susceptible to explosive spells.
Undead corpses that live in poisonous swamps. If you have a hard time hitting them, try psyching up first.
Fearsome demons capable of channelling the power of the underworld into a dazzling light attack.
Aristocrats of the monster world. Famed for doing the Hustle Dance when in dire trouble to tip the balance of a battle in their favour.
They often appear uninterested when first encountered, but, in reality, they are merely biding their time, waiting for the best moment to attack.
Ninja-like monsters that execute rapid turns and rush their opponents' legs in an attempt to trip them up.
A crafty monster that quietly observes its enemies to determine the weakest member of a party. Beware its talons.
Frog-monsters with strange patterns covering their bodies. When provoked to reveal the human faces on their backs, they can use powerful spells and ice attacks which damage the whole party.
To all appearances, these monsters look like nothing more than normal treasure chests. Try to open one, however, and the joke's on you. Beware the fearsome mimic!
In groups, these otherwise silly<->looking monsters are capable of playing melodies that can lay low even experienced adventurers.
Masters of the air, these monsters take flight on their leathery wings and attack foes from above.
Famed for launching into a strange dance that steals opponents' MP before running off. Although not particularly strong, these monsters can be quite annoying.
A monster whose enormous, flabby body and lolling tongue belie its intelligence. Generally uses spells to raise its attack power before unleashing a powerful strike.
These otherwise unassuming little lumps of flesh are in fact powerful magicians capable of casting both fire- and air-based spells.
Hyperactive monsters that live deep in forests. They swing their axes wildly as they charge their enemies.
Feisty monsters that resemble giant bulls. They paralyse opponents with Burning Breath before charging in for a ferocious attack.
Strike or slice these monsters all you want; their undead flesh feels no pain. Beware of their tendency to call in fellow ghouls to sway the odds in their favour.
It is said that these terrifying apparitions are born when the restless shadows of fallen monsters coalesce.

A killer suit of armour with a grudge against humanity. This monster boasts high offensive and defensive capabilities. Use support magic to subdue it before it uses its own magic to put everyone to sleep.
These massive slimes are theoretically capable of fully healing all of their allies in one go, but actual recorded cases are quite rare.
Humanoid nightstalkers that prowl the paths of the world, preying upon unwary travellers. Beware their dazzling light attacks and huge axes.
Though they are capable of casting spells, these monsters are rather more hocus-pocus than proper magicians.
These vicious monsters are masters of ice attacks. Their undead steeds appear to be made from the bones of lesser demons.
Ferocious insect monsters that love nothing more than tormenting humans. Fond of casting blinding spells and exhaling a venomous mist during combat.
The combined form of four smaller monsters: jab, ber, woc, and kee. In spite of their penchant for working together, they seem to be lacking in the team-spirit department.
These monsters use their hornpipes to herd wild sheep to lush green pastures. Their flocks are utterly devoted to them.
Bird-shaped killing machines. When attacks reduce their HP to a certain level, they self-destruct in an attempt to take their foes with them.
The undisputed master of puppeteers. The distinctive fire-spewing chimaera puppet is an original creation.
A monstrous scorpion that sends unwary travellers to an early grave. Highly resistant to fire<->based spells.
Born fighters, these monsters are masters of the Thin Air attack and highly resistant to air-based spells.
A silver beetle-monster. Protected by its iron-hard carapace, it can shatter boulders with a headbutt.
The physical manifestations of the flames of a subterranean volcano. Fond of using their scorching breath to give adventurers a warm reception!
Recent converts to the cult of the Lord of Darkness. Use magic to fell them quickly before they have a chance to curse you.
Acolytes of the Lord of Darkness that gave their own lives in sacrifice. Their flesh is gone, but their faith remains to fuel their hunger for battle.
Giant axe-toting dragons. Fond of using their scorching flame-breath to roast hapless travellers.
Aristocratic monsters. Using their spear tips, they trace their family crest in the air and unleash a powerful magical attack.
Green devils that make their homes in remote areas. They curse their foes with the point of a finger.
Although these monsters appear to be vicious and unthinking barbarians, they're actually masters of a spell which can resurrect fallen comrades.
A clump of souls fused into a hideous ball. These monsters are highly resistant to magic, so psyche up before attacking.
Silent and intimidating bird<->creatures that like to prevent their foes from using magic before attacking them with their razor-sharp talons.
Risen from the remnants of a magnificent ancient city. A visceral nostalgia for the days of old led bricks from the ruins to spontaneously reassemble themselves into human form.
Former priests of the cult of the Lord of Darkness. Their enslaved souls remain on earth to punish those who dare intrude into the Dark Ruins.
A bell made of ice. Those unfortunate enough to hear its chilling death-knell are frozen solid.
Originally created by a renowned Arcadian sculptor, these statues were so exquisite that they took on lives of their own.
Fly monsters that have a full command of the strongest ice magic. They live in cold areas, where they feast upon the frozen flesh of dead animals and unfortunate travellers.

A slime from the World of Darkness who has mastered the Slime Spank, a secret attack technique used only by slimes.
A fearsome foe indeed.
Said to be the soul of a man betrayed by his lover. The terrible pain of her deceit froze his heart and turned him into a vengeful monster.
Once ordinary wolves, now enslaved by an evil power. These unfortunate creatures tend to band together and live in packs.
Gruesome giants with grotesque smiles. They love to pound the enemy with their massive clubs, and, with their high HP, can take just as much damage as they deal.
A tension queen found in snowy mountain regions. Few can survive her Cool Breath when she's fully psyched up!
Ape monsters with fur as white as a blizzard. They pack snow into iceballs and furiously hurl them at enemies. Needless to say, their temper is hotter than their habitat.
Fly monsters that feast upon the flesh of fallen dragons. They are rightly feared as insect versions of bomboulders.
Invented by the infamous Dr. Dorte, these killing machines don't feel pity, remorse or fear. Once activated, they will not stop until every living creature within range has been terminated.
Ferocious ice-warriors born and raised in the deep mountain snow. Said to display a chilling hatred of all things warm.

Born from the darkness, these creatures jump from shadow to shadow to sneak up on foes.
Few physical attacks manage to touch them.
Travellers who happen to encounter this monster can't help chuckling. And if they're fortunate enough to defeat it, they can't stop smiling.
Born from silver frost, these ice-monsters live to punish those who hate snow and blizzards.
Beautiful masters of the skies. Beware their resistance to support spells and their ability to heal multiple allies simultaneously.
Pot-bellied monsters known for their scaly coats, which repel fire- and ice-based attacks.
Strange monsters that surround themselves with magic barriers to deflect spells. They are also associated with good luck; it is said that any who encounter them are sure to find true love.
A fearsome foe with multiple arms. Specialises in using several different weapons simultaneously! Tactically astute, and quick to exploit individual weakness.
A stone giant, formed from a headstone deep within the Dark Ruins that absorbed an evil soul and turned into a monster.
An evil bird-monster that flies through the skies of the World of Darkness. Casts powerful healing magic on itself and its allies when close to defeat.
An overweight warrior with a penchant for using magic to double its attack power. Fights like a real mucho macho man.
These dedicated and fiercely loyal monsters stood alongside Rhapthorne when the seven great sages first faced him down.
A fearsome tree of death. In the World of Darkness, trees grow from leaves rather than seeds, sprouting branches first and roots last.
A dragon warrior. Use magic to defend yourself against fire, lest you be consumed by their searing flame breath.
This foul demon is completely resistant to thunder-based attacks. Said to be a physical form of thunder itself.
A tiny star system from the World of Darkness. Emits an eerie light that makes enemies more vulnerable to spells.
Loyal creatures that have dedicated their lives to freeing Rhapthorne through macabre rituals ever since his imprisonment by the seven sages.
They may not look it, but the grim riders' donkeys are monsters in their own right. They are utterly dedicated to their riders.
Born from the toxic sludge of the dark seas. Prevents foes from attacking by singing funny songs and making them laugh.
These monsters combine the strengths of four-legged and winged creatures. Use physical attacks to defeat them as they are highly resistant to spells.
Once able to fly freely, these fearsome birds descended from the skies long ago to become swordsmen on terra firma. They taunt their foes by calling them ‘chickens’.
A flying alligator creature that uses its enormous weight to body<->slam unwary foes into submission.
A warrior beheaded in battle and risen again as a monster. Said to occasionally summon dark condors.
Frog monsters with two faces. The sight of the demonic faces on their backs is widely regarded as an omen of death by adventurers.
The number of eyes hidden under their masks constantly changes during battle. When they roll a six, expect to see a bomboulder join the fray.
A heligator that somehow lost its way, ended up in the World of Darkness, and began a new life as a darkodile.
A one-eyed giant possessing incredible strength. Fond of splitting the skulls of enemies with a swing of its enormous club.
Nightmarish creatures born from blood spilt on killing fields. They plunge battlefields into turmoil by beckoning other monsters into the fray.
Strange monsters that are animated forms of cursed rose bushes. They entwine enemies in thorny vines, then incinerate them with powerful fire spells.
A ferocious and powerful golden monster that grows even stronger when fighting alongside its friend, mohawker.
A silver-coloured comrade of buffalogre. This monster fights tactically, using powerful healing magic to turn the tide of battle in its favour.
Fearsome demons capable of casting some truly explosive spells. Some theorise that these monsters are the adult form of minidemons.
An overweight and cautious dragon. When threatened, it takes a swig of amor seco essence from its jar to restore its HP.
These dancers of the netherworld once played a central role in the rituals performed in honour of the Lord of Darkness. Experts in a wide variety of dance steps.
Aggressive monsters covered from head to toe in hard scales. They use magic to lower enemy defences before moving in for the kill.
Leaders of the troll world. Their imposing bulk translates into a massive amount of HP. Resistant to damage and difficult to defeat.
Treasure chests brought as tribute to the Black Citadel, transformed by the power of the Lord of Darkness into vicious monsters.
Bird-like monsters that patrol the halls of the Black Citadel. They carry swords consecrated by the Lord of Darkness himself.
Talented and trusted monsters that serve as guardians of Rhapthorne's throne. They are powerful indeed, with no weak points to speak of.
The fury of the Lord of Darkness taken physical form as a powerful monster. Combines sheer size and strength with an overwhelming hatred for anything human.
A beloved pet of Rhapthorne, this giant dragon swings its enormous tail to wallop multiple foes simultaneously.
A statue from the Black Citadel, risen to protect the Lord of Darkness in answer to devout believers' prayers.
An apostle of the Lord of Darkness who sacrificed his own life in order to serve his master. Calls upon other monsters to fight alongside him during difficult battles.
Powerful warriors, enslaved and imprisoned by the power of the Lord of Darkness long ago. Rhapthorne's awakening stirred them from their slumber.
Few travellers survive an encounter with these foul monsters, as every beat of their dark wings fills the air with a poisonous powder.
Firebirds born phoenix-like from raging infernos. Capable of exhaling an incinerating breath. Totally resistant to any fire-based attack.
Ferocious shadowcats that prowl through the darkness. It is said that no one who sets eyes on a dark sabrecat ever lives to tell the tale.
A strange pair of monsters living together in a symbiotic relationship. Said to drop an exceedingly rare pair of shoes when defeated.
These powerful dog-monsters are a handful in their own right, but become even more difficult to defeat when they call upon hell's gatekeepers for help.
Murderous monsters that slipped into another world during their search for prey. When in a state of high tension, they can fell even experienced adventurers with a single chop of their axes.
Fearsome demon-creatures belched from the depths of hell. It is said that they leave an eternal killing field in their bloody wake.
Almost nothing is known about these mysterious and phantasmal monsters who have a penchant for luring travellers to their death with an evil dance.
The mighty combined form of the head of state, the body politic, the right wing, and the other right wing...er, left wing. Feared for its mastery of lightning magic.
Like a demented jack-in-the-box, this well-camouflaged monster lives to surprise unwary travellers. Often carries precious materials that can be used in the alchemy pot.
Once a king amongst men. Killed during a crusade to destroy the world of dragons. His bitter soul bears a grudge against them to this very day.
A knight that traded his physical body for the power of the Lord of Darkness. Lofts his sword high in the air to call down a divine punishment upon his foes.
Undead creatures that torment enemies with an array of powerful and destructive breath attacks. Psyche up if you want any hope of landing a solid hit.
A general in the army of the underworld. Already powerful in its own right, after psyching up its attacks can injure entire parties with a single strike.
A mad planet with evil ambitions. Calls forth meteor storms to destroy any who dare oppose it.
An incredibly destructive monster with an attack power almost beyond imagination. Said to carry extremely rare seeds.
Fearsome magicians who hold the power of life and death in their cruel hands. Masters of magic, they are adept at casting every form of spell.
A monster that stands guard at the gates to the netherworld. Calls forth an elysium bird to drive your monster team back into reserve.
An enormous, airborne alligator creature with a cruel smile and a vicious chuckle. Beware its powerful body-slam attack.
The juvenile form of the same type of monster as Khalamari. Often tries to play with the enemy instead of attacking them.
A healer of the sea. Will often flee immediately after healing an injured comrade. Can be quite difficult to hit.
Their cute appearance belies the ferocity of their attacks. Known for preying upon ships at sea, which they surround and subdue with powerful paralysis spells.
A monstrous crustacean sporting an impenetrable shell. Parries attacks by flexing its body.
Like pop-stars of the deep sea, these vile vocalists call other monsters to their aid with their smooth singing voices.
A fish monster with a pig-like face. Its flesh is poison to anyone foolish enough to eat it.
The anchor of a ship that sunk with all hands on board, given new life as a vengeful monster. Launches itself from the sea bed in an attempt to bring other ships down to share its fate.
Expert healers of the sea. Focus your attacks on these monsters first, as they are capable of resurrecting fallen allies.
The juvenile form of the king squid. Not particularly interested in fighting. Think of them as the mascots of the sea!
Crayfish monsters covered in ultra-hard armour plates. Particularly resistant to air-based spells.
A monstrous form of moray eel that subdues enemies with a mouth full of poisonous fangs.
A fearsome hunter of the sea. Uses magic to decrease a foe's defence before slashing at it with its razor-sharp talons.
Feared by sailors, who also call these monsters ‘terror tentacles’. Due to the high HP of king squids, you may want to use instant-death spells rather than physical attacks to subdue them.
Highly trained warriors of the sea, equally adept at physical and magical combat. Difficult to defeat with physical attacks alone.
The tortured spirits of humans who perished at sea. Whenever a fellow monster dies, pigmalions almost inevitably sacrifice their own lives to resurrect their fallen allies.
Fearsome monsters of the deep sea. Capable of using Gigaflash to dazzle enemies. Remarkably agile and hard to hit.
Fearsome and angry wharf<->monsters. Use spells to attack them, as weapons have little or no effect on their tough steel bodies.
A monster resembling an enormous sea snake. Highly venomous, these monsters use their fearful appearance to confuse enemies during battle.
Evil mermaids that seduce and lure unwary sailors to their deaths with the tantalising promise of Puff-Puff delights.
An elite among mermen. The hard scales covering its body bestow complete resistance to fire-based spells. Beware of their high attack power.
Masters of breath-based attacks, these monsters use their fearful roar to intimidate enemies.
Long feared by sailors, these monsters use their vicious lances and lightning-fast reflexes to deprive unwary ships of treasure.
A fearsome fighter of the seas with razor-sharp claws. Capable of spinning its body like a propeller to cut the enemy to ribbons.
Rulers of the deep sea, these monsters boast incredible vitality. Generally speaking, they are nearly impossible to defeat with physical attacks alone.
Ferocious and hungry sea monsters. They wait in deep waters for ships to pass overhead, then launch themselves towards the surface to sink them.

A physical manifestation of fire magic. As this monster lacks a material body, most physical attacks pass right through it.
Try raising your tension when fighting them.
The soul of a slain traveller, endlessly wandering in search of its path back home.
Once the world's most powerful warrior, his abilities attracted Rhapthorne's attention and earned him a place as a sentinel of the Black Citadel.
In groups, these otherwise silly<->looking monsters are capable of playing melodies that can lay low even experienced adventurers.
A bell made of ice. Those unfortunate enough to hear its chilling death-knell are frozen solid.
Surprisingly bossy for a monster that is an incompetent fighter at best when alone. But it seems to have some sort of trick up its sleeve...
Although as stocky and strong as a sumo wrestler, this monster doesn't seem to be able to live up to its true potential on its own.
A right-handed monster that wields a sword far too large and heavy for it to handle well.
A left-handed monster that swings a single sword with both hands. The youngest of four brothers, it has an affinity for cheese.
The stubborn head of the mighty jabberwockee. An unyielding blockhead of a leader, famed for never having apologised for anything in its entire life.
The selfish body of the mighty jabberwockee. Deeply resents jab, kee, and woc for forcing it to carry them all the time.
The pompous right arm of the mighty jabberwockee. Never misses a chance to guilt-trip jab, ber, and woc into thanking it for its healing ability.
The egotistical left arm of the mighty jabberwockee. Constantly on the lookout for a chance to use its magic to speed itself up and flee.

The self-proclaimed brains of the team. Capable of casting both lightning<->based and healing spells. Boasts of being elected by its fellow party members. In reality, it was handed the position by their father.
The huge and sluggish body politic resists all but the most dedicated attacks.
Famed for chuckling evilly during battle. In reality, chuckles evilly all the time.
Incessantly complains about the activities of the right wing, body politic, and head of state, but lacks the motivation to actually do anything about it.
One of the guardians of the Doors of Judgement deep within the Dragon Graveyard. Has carried out his duty for too many years to remember.
One of the guardians of the Dragon Graveyard. Attacks candidates to test their worthiness to undertake the trial.
A bitter and vengeful merman who has long sought the tortune<->feller responsible for dropping a crystal ball on his head.
Although temporarily transformed into a ferocious brute by Dhoulmagus's enchantments, Khalamari is actually quite a kind fellow at heart. At one time he planned to open his own comedy club.
The cursed spirit of the abbot of the former abbey, which was destroyed after being stricken by the plague. Slaying this poor creature put an end to many centuries of suffering.
A monster that carries the precious Venus' tear in its mouth. Its guiding motivation appears to be its obsession with priceless jewels and treasures.
A self-proclaimed artist and music lover. Unfortunately for those around him, his love for music doesn't necessarily mean he's any good at it.
Long hunted for their precious Argon hearts, these monsters run at the first sight of humans.
The largest and most impressive Argon lizard. It's Argon heart is said to be pretty huge!
Once an ordinary jester, his theft of the sceptre from Trodain Castle gave him magical powers beyond imagination.
Jessica, with her mind enslaved by the evil will of the sceptre. Thankfully, the power of Dominico's magic aura restored her to her former self.
A legendary pirate who sailed the high seas in search of the world's most precious treasures. His trademark hat never goes out of style.
The Godbird, capable of travelling between worlds. Joined forces with the seven sages to imprison Rhapthorne long ago.
Rhapthorne's right-hand monster. Took Empyrea's egg hostage to force her to attack Dark Empycchu.
Dominico's beloved pet dog, transformed by the power of Rhapthorne's sceptre into a vicious monster.
Angelo's half-brother. Attempted to harness Rhapthorne's power, but ended up being enslaved by it.

The Lord of Darkness. His soul is imprisoned in the magical sceptre of Trodain Castle, while his physical form is entombed within the Goddess Statue on the Holy Isle of Neos. He dreams of ruling the World of Light.
The Lord of the Dragovians, who sacrificed his sanity in an attempt to abandon humanity. Returned to his senses through the efforts of <hero> and the party.
A giant dragon whose scales gleam with a fiery hue. Attacked <hero> and the party to test their courage and worthiness to bear the title of heroes.
A perfect likeness of <hero>, created by the evil powers deep within the Black Citadel. Now just a normal statue.
A perfect likeness of Yangus, created by the evil powers deep within the Black Citadel. Given life by Rhapthorne's foul ambitions, it attacked the party.
A perfect likeness of Jessica, created by the evil powers deep within the Black Citadel. Not nearly as squeezable as the real thing.
A perfect likeness of Angelo, created by the evil powers deep within the Black Citadel. Just as much trouble as the real thing!
One of the main guardians of Rhapthorne and the Black Citadel. Draws upon the power of the deepest, darkest seas to destroy the World of Light.
The ruin of the Black Citadel itself, risen to defend its master Rhapthorne from <hero> and the party!
Don Mole's loyal henchmen. Willing to endure anything for their boss... Except listening to his music, that is.
A giant dragon with scales of deepest forest-green. Fought <hero> and the party to draw out their full potential.
A giant dragon whose scales glitter like sunlight on a frozen waterfall. His cold gaze penetrated <hero> and the party during battle, judging their qualities and capabilities.
A golden dragon with scales as bright as the sun at the height of summer. His limitless willpower and reserves tested <hero> and party during a long and arduous battle.
A giant dragon with scales the colour of a dark and starless night. His seemingly limitless might took <hero> and the party to the brink of despair during battle.
A giant dragon enveloped in an aura of holy light. Challenged <hero> and the party to reach their true potential through an epic battle of divine wrath and mercy.
Like a phoenix from the flames, the Ultimate Dragon embodies the true power of the Lord of the Dragovians. The final Dragovian Trial.
DESCRIPTION OF restless armour: Lonely Joe
DESCRIPTION OF king kelp: Big Al
DESCRIPTION OF liquid metal slime: Metabble
DESCRIPTION OF boss troll: Pa Troll
DESCRIPTION OF metal king slime: Hev
DESCRIPTION OF bag o' laughs: Trick Bag
A beautiful, radiant bird that any birdwatcher would be delighted to spot...until it attacks!
A grim knight of the dead atop a hellish steed. His deft use of Multithrust soon sends his foes on a one-way trip to his homeland.
A revolting remnant of battle that dribbles a putrid puss from its lips. With Burning Breath it seeks to paralyse the party.
This resplendent statue of gold belongs at the gates of heaven. No one knows how or why it has fallen from grace.
Does it taste slimy or caramelly? That's the brûlé-ing question. Yet no one can answer it because no one has ever eaten one.
A mummy, not so much petrified as prettified, with a large pink ribbon and bow. But would anyone want to receive such a present?
An imp being impish by dressing up as Morrie. But it's not just the imp-osing outfit. Oh no, this cheeky devil is an imp-rovement on its brethren, with more GUSTO and more PASSION! So beware!
A candy cat coated in gold! In fact, it's so shiny, you shouldn't look straight cat it, for fear of clawsing damage to your eyes!
Everyone's favourite treevil when it's time to sit under the cherry blossoms in spring. But best observed from afar, since it will attack if it twigs you're there.
A spontaneous Xmas transformation of a hell hopper in a festive mood. Add a dead bowdy into the mix, and you've got a truly magical crimbo combo!
A chestful of trouble inside which chaos reins.
One of Rhapthorne's retainers, turned to stone by the great sages in a toilsome tussle, but now free from his seal once more. He welcomes <hero> and the party as a distraction from his imposed ennui.
A fabled chest that promises to deliver all who encounter it to the hereafter.
The first challenge you meet when you take a walk down Memories Lane. Not the sharpest tool in the box, but he'll wipe you out if you lake might of him.
Part of the second challenge that awaits down Memories Lane. Largely a healer for his cronies, for which he may employ Kazing, he may also injure the entire party with a single strike.
Part of the second challenge that awaits down Memories Lane. This rattling bag of bones likes to attack with his walking corpse companion.
Part of the second challenge that awaits down Memories Lane. This stinky stiff likes to attack with his skeleton sidekick.
The third challenge down Memories Lane <endash> another monster once slain by the party in the past, now back ‘in memoriam’ to deal a deadly concoction of critical hits and Whack wizardry.
The fourth challenge you encounter on a trip down Memories Lane. Don Mole's dead, but he still feels good. You knew that he would now. Oh yeah, he's duggone dangerous.
Don Mole's revival tour backing singers, joining him in the fourth challenge you encounter down Memories Lane. They're stouter and more soulful than ever, but can still be Dazzled.
The fifth challenge that a trip down Memories Lane leads you to. This great beast loves to scare the party stiff with its terrifying war cries.
Unlucky for some, the thirteenth challenge you encounter on a trip down Memories Lane consists of Dhoulmagus in triplicate <endash> one who attacks, one who heals and one who revives.
The fourteenth challenge you encounter on a trip down Memories Lane. In memoriam he may be, but this is Dhoulmagus in a most deadly form.
The eleventh challenge to present itself on a trip down Memories Lane. Sepia seems to suit her, and this Jessica can captivate men with complete consistency. The more women in the party, the better.
An extra in the eleventh challenge you encounter down Memories Lane, this shadow is never far behind Evil Jessica, but only manages physical attacks in the main.

The sixth challenge that awaits on a trip down Memories Lane. Even in memoriam Crow is still buckling swash, and enjoys giving a daring display of tension-building almost as much as receiving a puff-puff.

The seventh challenge you encounter on a trip down Memories Lane. For some reason <endash> perhaps cowardice <endash> he doesn't like to fight alone, and often summons his dark turkey and darkbird lackeys.
A member of the seventh challenge you encounter down Memories Lane, who quietly bolsters his feathered friends in battle with Multiheal and Kasap.
A cocky member of the seventh challenge you encounter on a trip down Memories Lane. He likes to stun the party into inaction with loud squawks.
The eighth challenge awaiting those who take a trip down Memories Lane. He uses a muttley assortment of breath attacks that hit the whole party. His weakness appears to be poison.

The twelfth knight <endash> or rather, the twelfth challenge to be faced down Memories Lane, in the form of the Templar Marcello. In memoriam, his battle devices of choice are Fizzle and sweeping attacks against the whole party.
The ninth challenge you encounter on a trip down Memories Lane. Together with its dancing flame flankers, it unleashes a deadly squall of Scorch and other attacks against the party.
A member of the ninth challenge you encounter down Memories Lane. Appearing with a servant of darkness, together they unleash a deadly squall of Scorch and other attacks against the party.

The tenth challenge that awaits those who take a trip down Memories Lane. Most attacks are futile against this impenetrable fortress of a foe, leaving only critical hits and defence-dodging strikes to play with.
DESCRIPTION OF phantom swordsman: Sir Bodless
DESCRIPTION OF wight king: Barry Wight
DESCRIPTION OF fencing fox: Michael J.
The final challenge that awaits at the very end of a long trip down Memories Lane. He knows his name is Estark, but beyond that, nothing...
Dhoulmagus, transformed by the awesome power of the sceptre. In spite of his new-found might, his lethal curses proved to have no effect on <hero>.

The Lord of Darkness himself, taken physical form, and grown powerful enough to absorb
the massive Black Citadel into his new body.
Though this behemoth effected his resurrection at the Altar of Wroth, <hero> and the party bested him...with a little help from someone's brother.
